article.headline: Dayton 57, Fordham 45
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Roberts scored 18 points to lead Dayton to a 57-45 win over Fordham Wednesday night. With the score tied 15-15 at 8:12 of the first half, the Flyers (15-8, 5-5 Atlantic 10) outscored Fordham 19-11 to go into halftime with an eight point lead. The Rams (13-9, 6-4) never held the lead in the second half as Dayton pulled ahead by as many as 14 points. Norman Plummer, who came off the bench, and Monty Scott each had 10 points and seven rebounds for Dayton. Marcus Stout, the only Fordham player to score in double digits, had 12 points. Sebastian Greene had nine rebounds and Bryant Dunston had seven for the Rams. Dayton shot 38.5 percent (20 of 52), while Fordham hit about 35 percent (17 of 48). Dayton scored on five of its 16 3-point shots, while the Rams hit only one of 15 attempts. Fordham held the advantage on points off turnovers with 11, compared to Dayton's two.
